                            <comment id="13893179" author="sauthieg" created="Thu, 6 Feb 2014 08:47:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is this really necessary to exposes theses internal classes/packages ?&lt;br/&gt;
Maybe we should use the service way:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;interface&lt;/span&gt; DeclarationService {
  InstanceDeclaration newInstance(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; name, &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; component);
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// Provide any other necessary/friendly methods
&lt;/span&gt;}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This way we can keep private all of our internal bits.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thinking aloud about this interface:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;does it need to expose an InstanceDeclaration or some kind of handle to the declaration (something that can be use to retract the declaration) ?&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;does it need to have some fluid API (something like what you&apos;ve done for the &lt;tt&gt;@Configuration&lt;/tt&gt; API) ?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;WDYT ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13895457" author="clement.escoffier" created="Sat, 8 Feb 2014 07:11:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I agree, our internal bits should be kept hidden. Adding a way to create InstanceDeclaration using a fluent API is definitely something interesting. In addition, as you said, we should be able to withdraw the declaration using the API. We can probably reuse the API we use in @Configuration, extended for the withdrawn case.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Do we need the same for types and extensions ?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Clement&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13895460" author="sauthieg" created="Sat, 8 Feb 2014 07:28:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll do some prototyping.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13898083" author="sauthieg" created="Tue, 11 Feb 2014 18:03:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m wondering if the created InstanceDeclaration should be modifiable after creation ?&lt;br/&gt;
Like renaming, changing properties, ...&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13900315" author="sauthieg" created="Thu, 13 Feb 2014 13:26:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve pushed some preliminary work around instance creation declaration in my github fork:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/sauthieg/felix/commit/f66d6a30c8975a5b711e33ba85d80143a0185269&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/sauthieg/felix/commit/f66d6a30c8975a5b711e33ba85d80143a0185269&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Take a look at &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/sauthieg/felix/blob/bug/FELIX-4419/ipojo/runtime/core/src/main/java/org/apache/felix/ipojo/extender/DeclarationBuilderService.java#L22&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/sauthieg/felix/blob/bug/FELIX-4419/ipojo/runtime/core/src/main/java/org/apache/felix/ipojo/extender/DeclarationBuilderService.java#L22&lt;/a&gt; for API usage example in the javadoc.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;WDYT ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13910289" author="sauthieg" created="Mon, 24 Feb 2014 13:23:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Pushed in trunk&lt;br/&gt;
Please close if satisfied&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13910303" author="clement.escoffier" created="Mon, 24 Feb 2014 13:40:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That&apos;s great, thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
